Q2:
The probability of two heads is 25%,
the probability of two tails is 25%,
the probability of one head and one tail is 50%,
It's different because when tossing two coins, he first coin can be head or tail, and the second coin can be head or tail, so there are four possibilities when tossing two coins. Thus, in two of four situations the result is one head and one tail, which is 50%.

